<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6259</anchor> <rss>jms-000B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-000B</addr>  <route>jms-000B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Category with zero morphisms</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em>category with zero morphisms</em> is defined to be a category <link href="jms-000H.xml" type="local" title="Enriched category">enriched</link> in the category of pointed sets and strict maps. The distinguished point of <tex>\mathbf{hom} _{ \mathcal{A} } { \left ( A , B \right )}</tex> shall be written <tex>0</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6260</anchor> <rss>jms-000H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-000H</addr>  <route>jms-000H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Enriched category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>{ \left ( V,I, \otimes , \alpha , \lambda , \rho \right )}</tex> be a <link href="jms-000D.xml" type="local" title="Monoidal category">monoidal category</link>. A <em>category <tex>C</tex> enriched in <tex>V</tex></em> is defined by the following structure and axioms:</p><ol>  <li>a collection <tex>\mathbf{ob} _{ C }</tex> of <em>objects</em>;</li>  <li>for any two objects <tex>x,y</tex>, an object <tex>\mathbf{hom} _{ C } { \left ( x , y \right )} \in  V</tex>;</li>  <li>for every object <tex>x</tex>, a morphism <tex>I \xrightarrow{i _{ x }} \mathbf{hom} _{ C } { \left ( x , x \right )}</tex> in <tex>V</tex>;</li>  <li>for all objects <tex>x,y,z</tex>, a morphism <tex>\mathbf{hom} _{ C } { \left ( x , y \right )} \otimes \mathbf{hom} _{ C } { \left ( y , z \right )} \xrightarrow{c _{ x,y,z }} \mathbf{hom} _{ C } { \left ( x , z \right )}</tex> in <tex>V</tex>.</li>  <li>    such that the following diagrams commute in <tex>V</tex>:
    <center><img src="resources/79add6da4c504794d99368640aecf914-web.svg"/></center>    <center><img src="resources/3fc6678c3ffa812beddd97c6819eb8eb-web.svg"/></center>  </li></ol></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6261</anchor> <rss>jms-0009.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-0009</addr>  <route>jms-0009.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Kernel</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathcal{A}</tex> be a <link href="jms-000B.xml" type="local" title="Category with zero morphisms">category with zero morphisms</link>. Then the <em>kernel</em> of a morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow{f}  B</tex> in <tex>\mathcal{A}</tex> is defined to be a morphism <tex>K \xrightarrow{k} {A}</tex> such that for any <tex>X \xrightarrow{h} A</tex> with <tex>h;f=0</tex>, there exists a unique map <tex>X \xrightarrow K</tex>factoring <tex>X \xrightarrow{h} A</tex> through <tex>K \xrightarrow{k} {A}</tex> in the sense of the diagram below:</p><center><img src="resources/85e6e8d9bc0320178253421df5cbfe61-web.svg"/></center></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6262</anchor> <rss>jms-000A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Notation</taxon> <addr>jms-000A</addr>  <route>jms-000A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Kernel</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>We will often write <tex>\operatorname{ker} {f} \xrightarrow{i _{ \operatorname{ker} { f } }} A</tex> for the <link href="jms-0009.xml" type="local" title="Kernel">kernel</link> of a map <tex>A \xrightarrow{f} B</tex> in a <link href="jms-000B.xml" type="local" title="Category with zero morphisms">category with zero morphisms</link> <tex>\mathcal{A}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>6263</anchor> <rss>jms-000C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>jms-000C</addr>  <route>jms-000C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>1</month> <day>18</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Kernels as equalizers</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Evidently, the <link href="jms-0009.xml" type="local" title="Kernel">kernel</link> of a morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow{f}  B</tex> in a <link href="jms-000B.xml" type="local" title="Category with zero morphisms">category with zero morphisms</link> is the <em>equalizer</em> of  <tex>A \xrightarrow{f}  B</tex> with the zero morphism <tex>A \xrightarrow{0}  B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>